DC  Aminosugars Metabolism
DR  KEGG; map00530;
CC  CMP-N5-acetylneuraminate (CMP-Neu5Ac) is the activated version of a
CC  sugar unit found in certain glycolipids and glycoproteins. Neuraminic
CC  acid is also commonly known as sialic acid. In particular, Neu5Ac is
CC  observed in certain versions of the E. coli O-antigen [1]. CMP-Neu5Ac
CC  is synthesized in three steps: isomerization of UDP-GlcNAc to
CC  N-Acetyl-D-Mannosamine (ManNAc) catalyzed by NeuC (5.1.3.14), a
CC  condensation with phosphoenolpyruvate to form NeuNAc catalyzed by NeuB
CC  (2.5.1.56) and an activation with CTPcatalyzed by NeuA (2.7.7.43). A
CC  fourth gene product, NeuD is believed to carry out O-acetyltransfers
CC  onto sialic acid but is often missing and is also found more broadly
CC  than NeuABC
--
